'''''Best Bits''''' is a New Zealand comedy show, where a panel of comedians comment on video clips taken from television during the week prior. It is produced by [[The Down Low Concept]], and hosted by comedian [[Te Radar]] in the first series and ex-''[[Seven Sharp]]'' presenter and comedian [[Jesse Mulligan]] in the second and third series.

The first series premiered on [[TV One (New Zealand)|TV One]] on 19 July 2013,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Eley|first1=Tom|title=Te Radar shows his Best Bits|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/tv-radio/8936157/Te-Radar-shows-his-Best-Bits | publisher = Stuff.co.nz | date = 19 July 2013}}</ref> and ended on October 2013 with "Best Bits of Best Bits", an episode where highlights from the past series were revisited. The second series premiered on 26 March 2014, and ended on 19 June 2014. The third series premiered on 26 February 2015, and ended on 21 May 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.stoppress.co.nz/blog/2014/11/tvnz-unveils-its-2015-lineup | title=TVNZ unveils its 2015 lineup | date=13 November 2014 | accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>
<!--The show is currently broadcast each Thursday at 9:35pm on TV One.-->

